To run this:

1. Edit the Makefile to make sure ``READS_DIR`` points to the directory where
the raw reads are.

2. Download Bowtie2 to the same folder where "IMM" folder is.

3. Depending on the desired analysis, run the following::
3.1. Human Genome (without mitocondrial DNA)
	cd Genome
	wget ftp://ftp.cbcb.umd.edu/pub/data/bowtie2_indexes/incl/hg19.1.zip
	wget ftp://ftp.cbcb.umd.edu/pub/data/bowtie2_indexes/incl/hg19.2.zip
	wget ftp://ftp.cbcb.umd.edu/pub/data/bowtie2_indexes/incl/hg19.3.zip
	unzip *.zip
	cd ../Human_DNA
	make 

3.2. Human mitocondrial DNA
	cd Mitocondrial_DNA
	make

3.3. Listeria RNA
	cd Genome	
	wget http://www.broadinstitute.org/annotation/genome/listeria_group/download/?sp=EATranscriptsFasta&sp=SLM_J0161_V8&sp=S.zip
	wget http://www.broadinstitute.org/annotation/genome/listeria_group/download/?sp=EATranscriptsGtf&sp=SLM_J0161_V8&sp=S.zip
	unzip *.zip
	../bowtie2-2.0.0-beta7/bowtie2-build listeria_monocytogenes_j0161_8_transcripts.fasta listeria_transcripts_j0161
	cd ../Listeria_RNA
	make
